Class RandomDeluxe

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Random

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class RandomDeluxe
extends java.util.Random
    The RandomDeluxe class extends java.util.Random adding a variety of utility methods, including those for use this Strings and arrays.

        public int nextInt(int min,
          int max)
        Get a random integer between two bounds. The bounds are allowed to be non-positive, but must have a positive difference.
        Parameters:
        min - The minimum (inclusive) integer value.
        max - The maximum (exclusive) integer value.
        Returns:
        a random integer in [min,max).
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if max <= min.

      • getRandomIndices

        public int[] getRandomIndices(int size)
        Get an array of integers from 0 to a specified number, randomly ordered. This method's name comes from the fact that it returns an array of random indices (if iterated through linearly) for an array of a given length.
        Parameters:
        size - The (exclusive) upper bound for the random integers.
        Returns:
        an array of integers on [0,size), randomly ordered.
